message: #12776 For the first time in 3 years of MIT education I notice that there are outlets in every seat of 10-250. Now I can die in piece.

#12755 Last summer I starved myself until I was underweight, weak, always cold, and had prominent bones. Now I’m binge eating girl scout cookies in my room, afraid to weigh myself because I’ve gained 15 lbs in the past six months. I know I shouldn’t do what I did when I was underweight, but my current habits aren’t much better. I hate that food controls me and I’m sad that the ED support group run by mental health isn’t happening this semester because I really really fucking need it.
